The paper discusses efficient algorithms for learning Generalized Linear Models (GLMs) and Single Index Models (SIMs), which are commonly used in machine learning and statistics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.ST (Statistics). The paper also involves optimization and computational efficiency, which suggests the possibility of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory) as potential categories.
